You can report progress by calling the `ReportProgress` method of the `BackgroundWorker` instance inside the `DoWork` method. The active BackgroundWorker instance is the `object sender` argument.

    private void Worker_DoWork(object sender, DoWorkEventArgs e)
    {
        // Get the BackgroundWorker that raised this event.
        BackgroundWorker worker = sender as BackgroundWorker;

        for (int i = 0; i &lt; (int)e.Argument; i++)
        {
            if (Running)
            {
                //Do work
                Thread.Sleep(10);  
                //Report Progress
                worker.ReportProgress(i);
            }
        }
    }

See documentation on microsoft Website : [BackgroundWorker DoWork Event](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.componentmodel.backgroundworker.dowork?view=netframework-4.8)

